# ------------ Newsletters Page "Les Echos" ------------#
This project implements a newsletters management page for Les Echos, allowing users to discover and subscribe to newsletters grouped by editorial site. The UI adapts dynamically based on the user's subscription rights displaying different CTAs depending on which newsletters they have access to.
|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||
## Tech Stack
Framework ::: Next.js 16 (App Router) ,
Language ::: TypeScript 5.7 ,
Styling ::: Tailwind CSS v4 ,
Fonts ::: next/font/google
|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||
## Architecture
app/
├── globals.css              # Design tokens (color system, font vars)
├── layout.tsx               # Root layout 
└── page.tsx                 # Entry point 

components/
├── newsletters-intro.tsx    # Static header
├── newsletter-section.tsx   # Section site
└── newsletter-card.tsx      # Individual newsletter card

lib/
├── types.ts                 # Shared TypeScript interfaces (Newsletter, User, Right...)

├── newsletters.ts           # Business logic (fetchNewsletters, hasAccess groupBySite)

├── utils.ts                  
└── mocks/
    ├── newsletters.ts   # Simulated API data
    └── user.ts          # Mocked user profiles
|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||
### Key Design Decisions

**Server Components first**
**CSS-native design tokens (Tailwind v4)**
**Profile simulation via URL**
The active user profile is driven by a `?profile=` query parameter (`one`, `multiple`, `none`), enabling reviewers to test all access scenarios without any UI toggle — keeping the page a pure Server Component with no client-side state.
|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||
## Getting Started
# 1---Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Wiem8/echos-next-test.git
cd nechos-next-test
# 2---Install dependencies
npm install
# 3---Start development server
npm run dev
==========>
Open [http://localhost:3000] in your browser.
### Testing Different User Profiles
Partial access ::: 1 subscription (RIGHT_1) ===> URL:::'localhost:3000'

Full access ::: 2 subscriptions (RIGHT_1 + RIGHT_2) ===> URL:::'localhost:3000/?profile=multiple'

No access ::: No subscription===> URL:::'localhost:3000/?profile=none'
## Available Scripts

npm run dev      # Start dev server with hot reload → http://localhost:3000
npm run build    # Production build
npm run start    # Start production server (after build)